responses.question: Are you talkative?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Yeah, i am, i am a very social  person and i love talking with people, but i hate when i meet someone who is ignorant as hell.」

responses.question: Are you reserved?
responses.response_open:
Luna: 「You mean do i keep to myself? Or do i share my thoughts and feelings with others?
I used to share everything with my sisters but now i feel like i cant trust them anymore because they just end up laughing at me and sharing my secrets with my father. When i was little i was very open about my feelings, but then people started calling me a crybaby and things like that for showing my emotions so i dont feel safe sharing my feelings anymore. So yes, you can say i am reserved.」

responses.question: Are you full of energy?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Always, i can't for the life of me stay still, my mother always scolds me  because she says i am too energetic and i always end up bumping into things and breaking them, but i can't control it, the energy just flows through me, i feel like i can jump in the air and fly all the way to the top of the castle...I have trouble sleeping because i just can't keep my mind still.」

responses.question: Do you generate a lot of enthusiasm?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Yes , i am very enthusiastic about everything. I am always excited about new things and projects i will be trying. When i find something interesting it catches my attention instantly and i start thinking about ways to improve it, how it works, how i can make more from it. Enthusiasm is one of my  most outstanding traits. I am very energetic and when i am excited about something it is hard to contain myself.」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant demonstrates high levels of sociability, energy, and enthusiasm. They express a strong desire for social interaction, high energy levels, and a keen interest in various activities, indicating a tendency towards extraversion.

responses.question: Do you tend to be quiet?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「I am when i am feeling down or anxious or scared, i find it difficult to speak because my chest is so tight that it hurts. When i am around people i never met before i am also nervous and i may be very quite at the beginning...But if i feel comfortable or if i am around people i know i will just never stop talking.」

responses.question: Do you have an assertive personality?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*firmly nods head* Yes, yes i do. I am firm and i usually get the outcome i want when i express my point of view. I want people to hear me and respect my opinions, so i make sure everyone understands how important it is for me. I want to make sure i put my message across, that everyone knows how i feel and that none of my thoughts or feelings are misunderstood or ignored.」

responses.question: Are you sometimes shy, inhibited?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「I am... *chuckles* Yes , yes i am. I really try not to show it but, when i am in front of people i dont know i get very shy. My heart starts beating too fast and i cant look people in the eye because of the anxiety. I can feel myself sweating  even though it isnt hot at all. I dont talk much and i am very stiff most of the time because of all the anxiety that is overwhelming me.」

responses.question: Are you outgoing, sociable?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「In someways yes... *chuckles  softly* I am an introvert by nature and i really like the privacy of being alone. I dont like spending time with people that i feel like dont respect or love me, but I am quite outgoing to people i get along with. I can be sociable sometimes but i need my alone time as well. I cant just be all sociable in a group of people that i dont really get along with, i just cant stand being around people that make me feel anxious, upset and judged.」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant seems to exhibit a mix of extraverted and introverted traits. They mentioned feeling quiet and shy in certain situations, but also expressed assertiveness and sociability in other contexts. It appears that the participant's level of extraversion may vary depending on their comfort level and the people they are interacting with.

responses.question: Are you depressed, blue?
responses.response_open:
Luna: 「*sigh* I wouldnt say i have depression, you are right i feel very down recently but depression is something too big to be thrown around like that. My life isnt as miserable as you think it is, i have servants who do my every bidding, i have a great life and i have everything i desire but...
Maybe i am depressed, maybe all the people around me being disappointed, annoyed or angry with me is getting to me...」

responses.question: Are you relaxed and handle stress well?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*chuckles* You have to be joking. I am the exact opposite of relaxed. You really think, someone who is being criticized from all around is relaxed? I cannot sleep at night because i am not sure what my father or my sisters or any other noble at court will say to me the very next day and what they will do to humiliate me  or punish me in some way, the stress is consuming me...」

responses.question: Can you be tense?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*giggle* I am tense like 90% of the time. Like i said before i am extremely stressed because my life is very unpredictable and things around me are always changing very rapidly so i always feel like i have to be on my guard. No other feeling can really compare to the dread i feel when i sense trouble is coming my way and i cant do anything about it.」

responses.question: Do you worry a lot?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Yes, all the time. I have so much to worry about. One day, it is my father being unhappy with me and wanting me to be "good" and "respectful" and other days i worry if my sisters are plotting something behind my back or if i am doing enough as a princess, or if my people are happy and healthy. As i already said before i am always worried, anxious and just stressed out from everything around me.」

details.analysis: The participant's responses consistently indicate high levels of anxiety, depression, stress, and worry. They express feeling down, stressed, and constantly on guard, which aligns with tendencies towards emotional instability and difficulty coping with stress.

responses.question: Are you emotionally stable, not easily upset?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*softly chuckles* No, not at all. I am prone to sudden outbursts of anger, sadness or anxiety. I can be fine one second and the next second i can just break down crying and not be able to control my emotions. I try to fight it but sometimes it just comes too fast.」

responses.question: Can you be moody?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*chuckles* Is it that obvious? I mean sometimes i feel like i am a bit too moody but i try to be more positive, most of the time i feel like my mood depends on my environment and the people around me. When i am alone i can be very calm and i sometimes feel relieved for being away from all that chaos outside, but whenever i go back out, all I feel is anxiety, sadness and stress...」

responses.question: Do you remain calm in tense situations?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*shakes head no* Not really, in those kind of situations i tend to be very overwhelmed and nervous. I hate confrontations and drama so in those tense  situations, I just want to be far away from the situation  and not be involved in it at all. Those kind of moments cause me a lot of anxiety and worry and i can never be calm when i am in the middle of those situations.」

responses.question: Do you get nervous easily?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*chuckles* Yes, i am a very nervous person by nature. I worry about everything constantly and it can be very exhausting sometimes. I want to be able to control my worries and stress but it can be hard sometimes, it is like all the things that could go wrong constantly run through my mind and i find it hard to relax even when nothing is wrong...」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant exhibits high levels of anxiety, moodiness, difficulty remaining calm in tense situations, and being easily nervous. The participant also experiences sudden outbursts of anger, sadness, and anxiety, indicating a lack of emotional stability and difficulty in controlling emotions.

responses.question: Do you do a thorough job?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Are you implying that i do a bad job? *sigh* You should see what i do behind the scenes, i am the one who takes care of everything. I manage the royal guard, i make sure that the queen,my mother, and the other princesses are taken care of and make sure they are safe and i also keep the king in check with his spending habits. But of course my father only sees my "rude side" because of how i talk to people and because my sisters tell him i am rude and ungrateful for everything they did for me, even though they didnt do much.」

responses.question: Can you be somewhat careless?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Careless? Oh yes, sometimes i am completely absent minded and end up forgetting things or making mistakes. I feel like my mind is running on 1000 different things at once and my body is running at 100km/h to keep up with my mind and in doing so my body ends up bumping into things, running into people, forgetting things or making simple mistakes that i would never make if my mind was at peace. Sometimes i even feel my head spinning from all the thoughts.」

responses.question: Are you a reliable worker?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「I like to believe that i am. Even though i may be stubborn and rude sometimes, i am dedicated to everything i do. No matter how i feel, if i am angry or upset i dont let that get in my way and i always give my very best in whatever i am doing. It is true that i am very strict with myself and sometimes with others, but it is the only way i feel things will get done correctly and to the best.」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant demonstrates a high level of dedication, striving for excellence, and a strong sense of responsibility. They express a strong commitment to their duties and responsibilities, despite occasional absent-mindedness and stubbornness. Overall, the participant's responses indicate a high level of conscientiousness.

responses.question: Do you tend to be lazy?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*laughs* I don't want to say i am lazy but sometimes i can feel pretty lazy. After a long hard day where i had to deal with my fathers anger, my mothers scolding and my sisters teasing i can just feel the exhaustion hitting me and all i can think about is lying in bed and not moving a muscle. But the things is that, even though it may be just my feeling, i am actually pretty hard working.」

responses.question: Do you persevere until the task is finished?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Absolutely. I feel like this is another one of my best traits. I wont quit until i finish whatever i set my mind to. Sometimes it may take days or even weeks, but i keep at it and i wont give up until i am done. I can be persistent and patient and i will put myself through hours of suffering if its necessary.」

responses.question: Do you do things efficiently?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Of course i do! As a princess who is expected to rule over the kingdom when she takes her father's place i always try to do everything as quickly and efficiently as possible. I always finish everything as soon as i start, i hate delays and i just cant stand it when people are late. To be honest, i even try to finish my tasks and to finish what i have to do before the time given. I hate delays  or things not going my way so i always try to get things done quickly and efficiently to avoid unnecessary delays and issues.」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant demonstrates a high level of self-discipline, perseverance, and efficiency in task completion. However, there are also instances where the participant admits to feeling lazy and exhausted after dealing with family conflicts. Overall, the participant's strong determination and efficiency in task completion outweigh occasional feelings of laziness.

responses.question: Are you easily distracted?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*giggles* Yes i am, i am easily easily distracted. I can be focusing on one thing and before i know it, my mind is already in another place far away from what I should be doing. Sometimes just seeing things that i like can distract me. I like to think that its just my imagination running wild and i am not distracted by silly things , but i have to admit that i can sometimes get way too distracted by things that aren not even that important...」

responses.question: Do you tend to be disorganized?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Yes, i am quite disorganized. I have a lot on my mind and it is always racing with ideas and solutions and different thoughts that i try to keep track of but it cant be done and i end up forgetting things and forgetting to do chores and appointments. I am working on myself and trying to be more organized but it is really hard when you have your mind running at 1000 different things at once and then a sudden idea just pops up...」

responses.question: Do you make plans and follow through with them?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*firmly nods head* Yes! Once i make a plan and a promise, i will always follow through with them. Whatever my promises involve, i always make sure I keep them in the end. My word is my bond and i hate not being able to do that. It makes me feel anxious and ashamed of myself when i dont keep my word so i am always careful when i make plans for things that involve other people, i always want to be reliable and trustworthy.」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant demonstrates a high level of self-awareness regarding their distractibility and disorganization. However, they also exhibit a strong sense of duty and reliability when it comes to following through with their plans and promises.

responses.question: Do you tend to find fault with others?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Of course i do because no one is perfect and everyone makes mistakes  and i always point them out to make them work on them but nobody takes my advices because i have a "rude way to talk" whatever that means.」

responses.question: Are you helpful and unselfish with others?
responses.response_open:
Luna: 「I love helping other. It always melts my heart when i see someone's face light up when i help them, and the feeling that someone needed me, that i mattered makes me so happy. I always want to do what is best for others even if that means i may get into some troubles, and i dont care about how i feel at all...
When other people are happy, i am happy.」

responses.question: Do you start quarrels with others?
responses.response_open:
Luna: 「Yeah, sometimes when someone pushes me too far i snap and i just 
let out all the stress and anger i contain inside of me on whoever was unlucky to get in my way. I dont even try control myself or think before i speak , it is like i was possessed by an evil demon who was trying to release all that pent up anger at just one person.」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant seems to exhibit a mix of high and low agreeableness traits. They demonstrate high levels of altruism and a strong desire to help others, which aligns with the agreeableness dimension. However, they also display tendencies towards finding fault with others and starting quarrels when pushed too far, indicating lower agreeableness traits such as antagonism and distrust.

responses.question: Are you generally trusting?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*chuckles* My trust has been broken too many times. After all the experiences i had with people, i can no longer trust anyone  or believe  anything they say to me. I am constantly doubting the intentions of anyone who gets close to me and i cant bring myself to trust them. I cant take any chances, i cant have my heart broken one more time.」

responses.question: Can you be cold and aloof?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*Nods again* I can be. Especially when i am upset or angry. I try to just shut down and pretend everything is fine, even if my heart is in pieces. I dont allow anyone to see me hurt or sad, it makes me feel embarrassed and weak.」

responses.question: Are you considerate and kind to almost everyone?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「I am actually, or, i at least try to be. I dont know why i am like this but i have a strong urge to be kind to everyone. Whenever i see someone struggling or feeling down, i feel like their pain is transferred to me and i want to give them kindness, i want to give them words of strength or just comfort them so that their pain goes away. I know it is weird and kinda stupid but i cant control it, i always feel so bad when i see people sad so i cant really bring myself to be unkind.」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant exhibits a mix of low and high agreeableness traits. The participant expresses a strong distrust towards others and a tendency to be cold and aloof when upset or angry, which aligns with low agreeableness. However, the participant also demonstrates a strong inclination to be considerate and kind to almost everyone, showing empathy and a desire to alleviate others' suffering, which aligns with high agreeableness.

responses.question: Do you like to cooperate with others?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*nods* I can be a very cooperative person with people i like and feel comfortable with, so long as they don't just boss me around and expect me to follow, i like to work together with people with whom i can have a equal ground. I can easily work with people who are kind to me but with people who are being unfair or disrespectful i can be very stubborn and i may not work with them at all...」

responses.question: Do you have a forgiving nature?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*takes a deep breath* I feel like my forgiving nature is both my strongest and weakest point. I try to always be understanding and forgive people for the things they do to me, i sometimes even try to find excuses for their behavior, i try to understand their point of view and see reason so that i can forgive them. I hate confrontation so i prefer not to keep grudges...」

responses.question: Are you sometimes rude to others?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*softly chuckles* Yeah, sometimes... I usually cant help but say rude things to people that i feel like are mean to me. I can be rude and dismissive if i dont know the person well and i can be a bit sarcastic to them as well. I sometimes have a hard time controlling my anger so i can be a bit rough with my words sometimes which comes off as rude.」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant demonstrates a mix of agreeable and disagreeable traits. They express a willingness to cooperate and forgive, which aligns with agreeableness. However, they also exhibit stubbornness and rudeness towards those they perceive as unfair or disrespectful, indicating a less agreeable disposition in certain situations.

responses.question: Do you come up with new ideas?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Yeah , i always do. I want to improve things at our castle, make the lives of my people better, improve diplomacy, be more careful with money but my father doesnt trust i can do any of those things, he doesnt like me so i dont think my ideas will be accepted.」

responses.question: Are you curious about many different things?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*giggles* Oh, i can say that i am one of the most curious people in the kingdom. I love learning new things and meeting new people and hearing their story, i love trying new things and getting a new perspective at things. It is true i have a lot to manage but i have an incredible memory and i always make time for new things. I read a lot of books and i am always learning new spells and new things about medicine and alchemy.」

responses.question: Are you ingenious, a deep thinker?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「I would like to believe i am. I like to think my problems through and think of  solutions, i love inventing and creating spells and potions, i like to think about  the way the world works, i like to think about people their true thoughts, feeling, motives and their desires. I love coming up with different plans in my head and trying to think of every possible outcome there can be and prepare a solution to every single possibility there is. I love thinking.」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant demonstrates a high level of openness. They express a strong inclination towards generating new ideas, being curious about various subjects, and engaging in deep, abstract thinking. Their interest in learning, trying new experiences, and exploring different perspectives further supports their openness.

responses.question: Are you inventive?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「YES!! I just have no words to explain how inventive i get sometimes. If i see something that could be improved my brain just goes straight to thinking of ways to make that particular thing better, more efficient and more effective. I always get sudden bursts of ideas that dont even come from this world, they are just...so weird. When i am out by myself i constantly make up new spells, potions, inventions and just new things that may be useful to people.」

responses.question: Do you value artistic, aesthetic experiences?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Oh yes, yes i do very much. I love art, i love beauty ,i cant resist things that are beautiful and pleasing to the eye, i just can't. When i am stressed or angry just thinking about beauty and how relaxing it feels to be surrounded by it really helps to calm me down. It is also one of the reasons i do all the things i do , i want to make the place i live in more beautiful and pleasant not for me but to make my people happy and make them see how beautiful our kingdom is, so that they are proud of it.」

responses.question: Do you prefer work that is routine?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*nods* Yeah, i enjoy working in a routine environment where everything has a set order and i know what I am supposed to do. Having a routine and knowing what you have to do from the moment you wake up is comforting because it is predictable. No surprises no stress and no random things happen. You can never go wrong with a routine.」

responses.question: Do you like to reflect, play with ideas?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*firmly nods head* Yes, i am an inquisitive person who enjoys learning new things and ideas and i think about them. I like to think of all possibilities that can happen and then analyze them, i try to think of the worst that could happen so that i have a backup plan if needed. I love playing around with different ideas, different scenarios and trying new things just because i can and because i enjoy playing with ideas and exploring what can be and what could be. I always have my mind running, with different thoughts racing through me.」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant demonstrates a high level of openness across multiple facets. They exhibit a strong inclination towards inventive thinking, a deep appreciation for artistic and aesthetic experiences, and a willingness to play with ideas and explore new possibilities. Although they mentioned enjoying routine work, their overall responses suggest a strong preference for novelty and unconventional thinking.

responses.question: Do you have few artistic interests?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*softly chuckles* No, not at all. I like to express myself through art. I love drawing, painting and sculpting. I love writing songs and poetry. I love creating new words and spells and coming up with different solutions so that i can better express myself through my art. I can literally spend hours and hours working hard on my art without even stopping until i am satisfied with the result...」

responses.question: Are you sophisticated in art, music, or literature?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*softly chuckles* I would like to think so. I have been studying, practicing and getting better at art, music and literature for years now. I am not an expert but i think i have been practicing enough to be considered sophisticated in those fields...」

responses.question: Do you have an active imagination?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Oh yes, very. My imagination is something that takes me away from all the bad things happening around me, it lets me imagine myself happy, being accepted by everyone and  being respected by my father. It lets me imagine living a normal life, with a happy family and  not dealing with all the problems and stress... It lets me imagine myself far away from all the chaos my life has become...」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant demonstrates a strong inclination towards the facets of Fantasy, Aesthetics, and Ideas within the Openness dimension. They express a deep appreciation for art, music, and literature, actively engage in imaginative activities, and exhibit a strong desire for unconventional ideas. Additionally, their willingness to spend extensive time on their art and their self-perception of sophistication in artistic fields further supports their openness to new experiences and unconventional thinking.
